com.ephesoft.dcma.core.threadpool

Class EphesoftProcessExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ephesoft.dcma.core.threadpool.AbstractRunnable
      • com.ephesoft.dcma.core.threadpool.EphesoftProcessExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class EphesoftProcessExecutor
extends AbstractRunnable
    Class to execute and a control a process. This class provides proper retry mechanism if process fails to execute and wait time property which defines maximum time to wait for a process to execute completely. If process can't execute within wait time then process will be terminated and process will be re run by executor.
